abstract: The former Florida governor is finding a steady source of income in speeches for corporations, industry trade groups and other organizations.
snippet: The former Florida governor is finding a steady source of income in speeches for corporations, industry trade groups and other organizations.
lead_paragraph: In his final year as governor, Jeb Bush led a campaign to persuade an Italian military contractor and its partners to build a plant in Florida, meeting with the company’s chief executive, offering financial incentives and appearing at an event celebrating the project.

abstract: DeGroff on the best cocktails when traveling, and New Orleans and New York drinking cultures.
snippet: DeGroff on the best cocktails when traveling, and New Orleans and New York drinking cultures.
lead_paragraph: Dale DeGroff is one of the world’s foremost cocktail experts. His book “The Craft of the Cocktail,” published by Clarkson Potter in 2002, is regarded as an essential bartending guide. He is the founding president of the Museum of the American Cocktail in New Orleans, which reopened earlier this year. Mr. DeGroff is also a consultant working with bars and restaurants through the Beverage Alcohol Resource group, including the new Oleanders in Brooklyn.

abstract: News of a mass shooting in Charleston, S.C., has rippled across the campaign trail and prompted candidates to weigh in, the trade fight has helped shift focus from a Democrat-led filibuster in the Senate, and Senator Rand Paul is looking to a social media app to woo young voters.
snippet: News of a mass shooting in Charleston, S.C., has rippled across the campaign trail and prompted candidates to weigh in, the trade fight has helped shift focus from a Democrat-led filibuster in the Senate, and Senator Rand Paul is looking to a soci...
lead_paragraph: Good Friday morning from Washington, where news of a mass shooting in Charleston, S.C., has rippled across the campaign trail and prompted candidates to weigh in, the trade fight has helped shift focus from a Democrat-led filibuster in the Senate, and Senator Rand Paul is looking to a social media app to woo young voters.

headline_main: Today in Politics: Charleston Shooting Leads to a Campaign Pause

abstract: News of a mass shooting in Charleston, S.C., has rippled across the campaign trail and prompted candidates to weigh in, the trade fight has helped shift focus from a Democrat-led filibuster in the Senate, and Senator Rand Paul is looking to a social media app to woo young voters.
snippet: News of a mass shooting in Charleston, S.C., has rippled across the campaign trail and prompted candidates to weigh in, the trade fight has helped shift focus from a Democrat-led filibuster in the Senate, and Senator Rand Paul is looking to a soci...
lead_paragraph: Good Friday morning from Washington, where news of a mass shooting in Charleston, S.C., has rippled across the campaign trail and prompted candidates to weigh in, the trade fight has helped shift focus from a Democrat-led filibuster in the Senate, and Senator Rand Paul is looking to a social media app to woo young voters.

lead_paragraph: Jonathan Galassi, the longtime head of Farrar, Straus & Giroux, didn’t stray far for the setting of his first novel, “Muse,” which takes place in the world of New York publishing. (Erica Wagner reviews “Muse” this week.)

abstract: The economy of Dannemora, N.Y., a town near the Canadian border, revolves around the Clinton Correctional Facility, the maximum-security prison from which two inmates escaped last week.
snippet: The economy of Dannemora, N.Y., a town near the Canadian border, revolves around the Clinton Correctional Facility, the maximum-security prison from which two inmates escaped last week.
lead_paragraph: DANNEMORA, N.Y. — The most striking thing — the only striking thing, really — about the village of Dannemora, nestled in the Adirondacks, is a monolithic wall that both defines and divides it.
